member.name: T:Siemens.Engineering.Private.ProcessHelper
member.summary: The failure of several behaviors provided by 'System.Diagnostics.Process' motivated this class. On OS's supporting UAC accessing a process running with elevated privileges from an application running at lower privileges causes 'Process.MainModule' to fail. There are several issues using 'Process.WaitForExit' and 'Thread.Abort' together. The 'Process.Exited' event doesn't work correctly, ..., etc. This helper is meant to handle these error cases for the user.

member.name: M:Siemens.Engineering.Private.ProcessHelper.#ctor(System.Diagnostics.Process)
member.summary: Constructor that takes a process to be associated with this class.
member.param: The process to be used in association with this class

member.summary: Kills the process

member.name: M:Siemens.Engineering.Private.ProcessHelper.GetFileName
member.summary: Gets the file name used to start the process. The failure of Process.MainModule on OS's supporting UAC when the process is running at elevated privileges (administrator) relative to our own is one of the motivations for this class. We must revert to the Windows API function in these situations
member.returns: The file name used to start the process.

member.name: M:Siemens.Engineering.Private.ProcessHelper.GetHasExited
member.summary: Gets the exited state of the process. The failure of Process.HasExited on OS's supporting UAC when the process is running at elevated privileges (administrator) relative to our own is one of the motivations for this class. We must revert to the Windows API function in these situations
member.returns: Exited state of process.
